@node paula "PAULA Rulez"



PAULA Rulez
-----------

Do tego artykuîu zmusiîy mnie dwie przesîanki:
1.Pierwsza jest doôę bîaha, dotyczy mianowicie pojawienia sië na rynku
  kilku bardzo dobrych wielokanaîowych Trackerów na Amigë.
2.Druga przesîanka zostaîa spowodowana wypowiedziami i artykuîami 
  fachowców z róűnego rodzaju Secret Service, Gamblerów czy innych tam
  Catsów na temat wyűszoôci Klonów nad muzykâ Amigi.

  No dobra muszë stwierdzię, űe od stycznia anno domini 1995, przewaga
  Klona (i jego wszystkich kart w kupë wziëtych do 10 mln. zî - czyli
  domowych, inna sprawa czy karta za 9 mln. zî jest kartâ domowâ ?, na
  pececie karty te, moűecie mi wierzyę, nadajâ sië tylko do uűytku
  domowego, a űe kosztujâ od cholery, to juű inna rzecz) koďczy sië. 
  Nie porównujë, oczywiôcie, bardzo drogich kart takich jak SUNRise na 
  Amigë czy Roland na Peceta - bo nie o to w tym chodzi, by opisywaę 
  sprzët nie osiâgalny dla normalnego, ôrednio nadzianego czîowieka. 
  Porównujë natomiast kartë na Klona (do 5 mln. zî) + najlepsze
  trackery na ten sprzët (Scream Tracker, Fast Tracker - takűe wersja
  z poczâtku 1995) z programami Tracker na Amidze - SYMPHONIE i inne.

Co  sprawiîo, űe Amiga, wyposaűona w stary ukîad dúwiëkowy PAULA nagle
staîa  sië  taka  EXTRA.  Sprawiîo  to oczywiôcie oprogramowanie na A1200 i
A4000.

Pierwszym  programem,  który  zrewolucjonizowaî  caîkowicie rynek programów
muzycznych  na  Amigë byî oczywiôcie tracker SYMPHONIE, wspomnë, űe program
ten odpala 16 kanaîów muzycznych, w 8, 9 lub 14 bitach! o innych bajerach
nie  wspomnë ! Autor tego programu udowodniî, űe programy typu Tracker szîy
w  zîym kierunku, promujâc tylko standardowe kanaîy Pauli. Niestety program
ten  wymaga bardzo dobrej i szybkiej Amigi (co najmniej A1200/68030 25Mhz +
6 Ram).

Zaczëîo  sië  od  Symphonii,  obecnie  na  rynku pojawiîy sië zupeînie nowe
programy,  takie  jak  CYBERTracker czy  Art  of Noise. Wymienione
programy nie majâ takich duűych wymagaď i majâ szansë przyjâę sië na scenie
trochë dîuűej.

Co tu duűo pisaę NOWA ERA DOPIERO SIË ROZPOCZYNA !

Ps.Swojâ  drogâ  fakt  pozostaje  faktem,  űe  ciâgle  Macintosh  pozostaje
najlepszym komputerem dla profesjonalnego muzyka.

Ps.Uwaga  Muzycy !  swapperzy ZIG ZAGa wysyîajâ wymienione w artykule
programy (wersje demonstracyjne), wystarczy przesîaę dyskietkë z ciekawym 
stuffem i juű !


Opracowanie IREK P/UNN


Krótka NOTKA o nastëpcy ProTrackera ART OF NOISE 1.5
----------------------------------------------------


AON offers you:

	- OS2.0 look! no hardware hacking like in protracker
		- Reqtools filerequesters
		- CPU or copper viewmode split (for pattern-display)
		  (cpu needs more rasttime, but is more system-friendly)

	- More instruments!! (up to 61!!) (1-9,a-z,A-Z)

	- More patterns (up to 128) (if you demand more, just
	  tell me!)

	- More song-sequences (Song-Length now up to 256)
		- Restart-Position <>0 possible
		- nice sequence-list editor
		- new songlist-edit short cuts

	- More player-commands !! (increased to max. 62, 46 are already
	  in use!)
		- Arpeggio (up to 16) + Any other effect possible
		  each arpeggio can have up to 7 partnotes, arpeggio
		  speed is of course changeable
		- wavetable-commands
		- syndrums-commands
		- new effects like vibrato&volume set/slide etc..
		- external program SYNCHRONISATION commands (demos/games
		  and other presentations (easy to use for e.g. multimedia
		  productions, which shall be timed with the soundtrack)
		- 8 channel control commands
	
	- More notes ;) !!! Highest note is now B-5 !!

	- Maximal instrument play-length up to 256k, waveform size
	  only limited to free memory!!

	- Cool new sampler with lots of new effects (digital filter,
	  flanger/phase distortion/multi-sampling+triggering etc..

	- REAL 8 CHANNEL-MODE, *ALL* effects are usable on splitted
	  channels, that includes loops as well as FULL VOLUME&PITCH
	  control !!!
		- mix-rate up to 64khz!!!

	- Volume-Envelopes for SAMPLES(!!!) and WAVETABLE INSTRUMENTS(!)
	
	- Wavetable-Instruments !! ('synthetic' mode)
		- SAVES really A LOT OF MEMORY
		- no disturbing white noise, just crystal clear sound !!

	- Instrument&Waveform are seperated, so that e.g. 10 instruments
	  can use the same waveform (very useful!)
		- saves memory
		- create new sound-fx by using different instruments
		  which still use the same waveform!!

	- FM-Synthesizer
		- 2 operators to create cool filter-like sounds!

	- drumsequencer
		- create your own drumlines with up to 16 tracks
	  	- mixed in 16bit for optimal quality !
		- selectable pitch & sequence-length

	- Song-Remark can be detached to every song-module
		- up to 32k (even for small novels ;) )

	- Instrument names now up to 32 chars
		- easy instrument-selecting from the pull-down menu
		  (just click on the name !) or press amiga+(instr.nr)

	- Disable not-needed-song-info saving (like remark/instrument
	  names etc..
		- saves memory (about 3-36k)

	- Protracker-(load format)-compatibility, all key-shortcuts
	  in AON are just the same as in protracker (+ ofcourse a lot
	  of new shortcuts)

	- module-crunch
		- powerpacker
		- STONECRACKER (the best (fastest+most efficient)
		  cruncher around!)

	- memory usage e.g. for patterns is the same as in protracker,
	  although there are many many new improvements !!

	- many new pattern-edit commands !
		- exchange tracks/patterns
		- change volume
		- wildstar-replace (like in any texteditor!!!!)

	- player is easy to include in own productions (saves player+mod
	  files and executables )

	- for the interested guys: The fileformat is MUCH better than
	  protracker (well, it wasn't so hard to improve THAT format ;))
		- Chunk-format (like e.g. IFF)
		- easy to expand (future versions...)




I COÔ JESZCZE o ART OF NOISE
----------------------------

								

FEATURES OF AON
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
First  of all, it is 100% protracker compatible (load-format !) That means,
that  you  don't  have  to  get  used  to new shortcuts to old (protracker)
functions  !  But  that  doesn't  mean,  that  this tracker is just another
protracker  clone!  You might already have noticed, that AON has got dozens
of  new  functions. If you load AON for the first time, you might be slayed
by  all  these new functions, but it's worth taking a look at them. I think
it would be the best to list up a few of them:

- OS-2 graphical environment !  Reqtools-Requester !
- Supports euro-72 monitors !!
- 8 channels! But in contrary to startrekker/octamed/oktalyzer this time
  REAL 8 channels, that means free volume/pitch-settings on EVERY channel,
  loops ofcourse also possible !
- maximal number of instruments increased to 61 !
- maximal number of patterns increased to 128 !
- maximal number of positions increased to 256, including restartposition !!
- wavetable & sampleinstruments.
- 'macro' instruments possible: E.g. 10 instruments can share the
  same waveform, but the samplestart (for example, there is certainly
  a greater number of possibilities offered by this feature!) can
  vary from instrument to instrument ! Wavetable instruments can be
  used to create 64er-like sounds, but they are also great for big
  resonance-pads etc. !!
- number of player-commands increased from 28 (protracker) to 45 ! And
  there are ofcourse a lot to come in future versions !
- Supports powerpacker and STONECRACKER (the best cruncher around!)
- Arpeggio (maximal 7 notes!) + any other effect, arpeggio speed changeable
- Remark (normal textfile/ansi) linkable to module !!
- FM-Synthesis !
- Drumsequencer! Make your own drumlines with up to 16 tracks !!
- Big sampleeditor ! Features samples>128k, multisampling, sample-trigger
  digital-filter with selectable depth, flanger, phase-distortion, direct
  'freestyle' sampleediting: paint your own waves !
- supports external-synchronizing, e.g. for demos or other presentations!
- Player is easy to build in in own programs.
- Turbo-Player available, takes about 1-2 rasterlines (faster than any
  other player!)
- Update service for future versions!



When is the full version going to be released ?!

Yes, the full version IS AVAILABLE NOW!!
Just contact me at the address in the info-screen (in AON) or at the
address following later in this text.
